The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Sourav for NCA camp
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Sourav for NCA camp
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Sourav Ganguly has been asked to report at the NCA in Bangalore on Monday for a fitness and physical conditioning camp for Indias tour of Sri Lanka starting on July 18. Sourav, who will be overseas, has told the Board that he will report on Wednesday.         
	The camp will continue till June 30. India will play three Tests and five one-day Internationals in Sri Lanka, apart from two tour matches.                     
	Golf: PGTI Players Championship at RCGC from 7:30 am.                                                                                                                          
